00:28:58.940 --> 00:29:00.915
We do a lot of mitochondrial
DNA on the Basque.

00:29:00.915 --> 00:29:03.480
I study the Basque
in my lab as well

00:29:03.480 --> 00:29:05.090
and we have some
projects on them.

00:29:05.090 --> 00:29:06.867
But anyway, the
mitochondrial DNA

00:29:06.867 --> 00:29:08.450
is something you get
from your mother.

00:29:08.450 --> 00:29:10.457
We can do lineage
stuff, and it can

00:29:10.457 --> 00:29:12.290
be used when there's
just a fragment of hair

00:29:12.290 --> 00:29:14.770
or the body's very
decayed or burned.

00:29:14.770 --> 00:29:20.130
And Donald Denman-- this is
from the Albuquerque journal.

00:29:20.130 --> 00:29:21.170
He went missing.

00:29:21.170 --> 00:29:23.075
