boyfriend of a couple weeks.

00:34:03.590 --> 00:34:05.630
They picked it up 46
days after the murder,

00:34:05.630 --> 00:34:07.220
after the teams had been
through a couple times.

00:34:07.220 --> 00:34:08.040
They said they forgot it.

00:34:08.040 --> 00:34:09.330
I could show you
the collection film.

00:34:09.330 --> 00:34:10.120
They actually have it.

00:34:10.120 --> 00:34:10.929
They're passing it around.

00:34:10.929 --> 00:34:13.239
They're touching it, passing
it from one guy to another.

00:34:13.239 --> 00:34:14.905
And then they put it
back on the ground,

00:34:14.905 --> 00:34:16.889
because they forgot
to photograph it.

00:34:16.889 --> 00:34:18.739
So here they are, totally
in the bunny suits

00:34:18.739 --> 00:34:20.760
and they're putting
evidence on the ground.

00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:22.310
And they said they're
changing their gloves

00:34:22.310 --> 00:34:23.500
and the gloves are
clean and we had

00:34:23.500 --> 00:34:24.958
evidence their
gloves aren't clean,

00:34:24.958 --> 00:34:26.840
and we showed all that video.

00:34:26.840 --> 00:34:30.100
That's the knife that
supposedly Amanda used.

00:34:30.100 --> 00:34:33.560
And that's where DNA consistent
with the victim was found.

00:34:33.560 --> 00:34:37.100
This is the electropherogram
of that DNA from the victim.

00:34:37.100 --> 00:34:41.460
What is important here
is that the y-axis, which

00:34:41.460 --> 00:34:44.159
the FBI at that time wouldn't
look at anything below 200,

00:34:44.159 --> 00:34:46.900
there's only one
peak above 100 here.

00:34:46.900 --> 00:34:48.400
They were never
able to repeat this.

00:34:48.400 --> 00:34:52.850
It was an invalid procedure
and that's why she's free.

00:34:52.850 --> 00:34:55.000
We repeated this in my lab
as we were studying it.

00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:58.734
We collected soda cans from
the dean's office at lunch.

00:34:58.734 --> 00:35:00.900
And then I told my people,
save money on the gloves,

00:35:00.900 --> 00:35:02.850
just like they apparently did.

00:35:02.850 --> 00:35:03.892
Don't change your gloves.

00:35:03.892 --> 00:35:05.558
Change in every other
piece of evidence.

00:35:05.558 --> 00:35:06.980
Collect a can, go
in another room,

00:35:06.980 --> 00:35:09.300
and unpack a knife
from the Dollar Store

00:35:09.300 --> 00:35:10.980
and put that in a
separate evidence bag.

00:35:10.980 --> 00:35:12.620
Keep everything separate,
then change your gloves.

00:35:12.620 --> 00:35:13.960
Do it for five people.

00:35:13.960 --> 00:35:15.640
We did it for five
people and we found

00:35:15.640 --> 00:35:17.830
one person's DNA
transferred to the knife--

00:35:17.830 --> 00:35:19.950
one out of the five.

00:35:19.950 --> 00:35:23.150
I'm going to skip through this
just because we're at the end.

00:35:23.150 --> 00:35:24.750
So, happy ending.

00:35:24.750 --> 00:35:25.496
There we go.

00:35:25.496 --> 00:35:27.370
Amanda, that's a few
weeks after she got out.

00:35:27.370 --> 00:35:29.300
We had Thanksgiving
together at her house.

00:35:29.300 --> 00:35:33.210
And then both of our
families went rafting

00:35:33.210 --> 00:35:36.090
for three days in Idaho.

00:35:36.090 --> 00:35:38.380
I'll show you one more
example of how this can go.

00:35:38.380 --> 00:35:40.190
And somebody's going
to have to shoot

00:35:40.190 --> 00:35:44.150
me to get me off the stage.

00:35:44.150 --> 00:35:47.130
I mean a photograph.

00:35:47.130 --> 00:35:49.980
My mom lived in Europe, so I
followed this story for years.

00:35:49.980 --> 00:35:52.640
For 15 years, this woman
was committing crimes

00:35:52.640 --> 00:35:53.830
all over Europe.

00:35:53.830 --> 00:35:55.090
Rarely was there a witness.

00:35:55.090 --> 00:35:57.190
There's a murder.

00:35:57.190 --> 00:36:01.060
There are Romany
chiefs, feuding Gypsies

00:36:01.060 --> 00:36:04.520
who use guns and her DNA
is found on the guns.

00:36:04.520 --> 00:36:05.020
She robs.

00:36:05.020 --> 00:36:06.480
She injects herself with heroin.

00:36:06.480 --> 00:36:08.662
They found syringes
with her DNA.

00:36:08.662 --> 00:36:10.370
Kills with almost
professional precision.

00:36:10.370 --> 00:36:13.000
As far as German detectives are
concerned, she has no identity.

00:36:13.000 --> 00:36:15.200
They test 800 women
in Heidelberg.

00:36:15.200 --> 00:36:17.500
They do DNA test on
her-- nothing, no match.

00:36:20.010 --> 00:36:22.300
Bruno Bosch says in
2008 he's traveled

00:36:22.300 --> 00:36:26.310
60,000 kilometers questioning
witnesses-- nothing.

00:36:26.310 --> 00:36:28.240
They did 800 women,
as I told you.

00:36:28.240 --> 00:36:34.551
And in the end, it was a woman
who worked in the Bavarian swab

00:36:34.551 --> 00:36:35.050
factory.

00:36:37.720 --> 00:36:40.340
She was leaving a little
something on her swabs.

00:36:40.340 --> 00:36:41.970
That's the Phantom of Heilbronn.

00:36:41.970 --> 00:36:43.700
Why wasn't this detected?

00:36:43.700 --> 00:36:46.960
Because we don't track our
errors in forensic science.

00:36:46.960 --> 00:36:49.170
And I'll show you my
lab's answer to that.

00:36:49.170 --> 00:36:53.050
We study the smallest sequences
that don't exist in nature.

00:36:53.050 --> 00:36:54.480
We call them nullimers.

00:36:54.480 --> 00:36:57.990
For DNA, they were
recently 13 bases long.

00:36:57.990 --> 00:37:00.320
For proteins, they were
five amino acids long.

00:37:00.320 --> 00:37:01.770
And we call them nullimers.

00:37:01.770 --> 00:37:05.020
And we've made cancer-killing
agents out of the proteins.

00:37:05.020 --> 00:37:08.200
But out of the DNA,
what we've done

00:37:08.200 --> 00:37:10.390
is we've made a marker
that amplifies better

00:37:10.390 --> 00:37:12.560
than any of the human markers
and it looks like this

00:37:12.560 --> 00:37:13.480
on an electropherogram.

00:37:13.480 --> 00:37:15.396
Those are human markers
that have been diluted

00:37:15.396 --> 00:37:18.300
100,000 times after PCR.

00:37:18.300 --> 00:37:20.110
And then we diluted
it a million times

00:37:20.110 --> 00:37:23.160
and tried to PCR up everything,
all the human markers

00:37:23.160 --> 00:37:25.620
and our nullimers,
put it on a knife,

00:37:25.620 --> 00:37:26.912
and you can still see that.

00:37:26.912 --> 00:37:29.120
And so that means when you
give a swab to the police,

00:37:29.120 --> 00:37:33.085
at least one thing we can avoid
is they make a billion copies.

00:37:33.085 --> 00:37:34.210
That's what I do in my lab.

00:37:34.210 --> 00:37:35.960
You give me DNA, I
make a billion copies--

00:37:35.960 --> 00:37:37.310
first thing I do.

00:37:37.310 --> 00:37:39.220
Each of those copies
is indistinguishable

00:37:39.220 --> 00:37:41.404
from the original in PCR.

00:37:41.404 --> 00:37:43.070
It's not like a
traditional fingerprint.

00:37:43.070 --> 00:37:45.849
The Supreme Court got that wrong
when they said that it's just

00:37:45.849 --> 00:37:47.140
like a traditional fingerprint.

00:37:47.140 --> 00:37:48.810
We can take them from arrestees.

00:37:48.810 --> 00:37:49.310
It's not.

00:37:49.310 --> 00:37:53.150
I make a billion copies and one
of those copies in an aerosol,

00:37:53.150 --> 00:37:56.610
on a tube, on a glove,
is enough to convict you.

00:37:56.610 --> 00:37:59.330
And that's why we've
invented the nullimer marker.

00:37:59.330 --> 00:38:01.070
So I'll skip all this.

00:38:01.070 --> 00:38:03.680
If you're interested more in
hearing-- because we're out

00:38:03.680 --> 00:38:04.990
of time, right?

00:38:04.990 --> 00:38:08.750
You can read my book or contact
me at hampikian@yahoo.com.

00:38:08.750 --> 00:38:09.658
Thanks.

